view.name: MTA Subway Stations and Complexes
view.description: A dataset listing all subway and Staten Island Railway stations, with data aggregated by station complex. This dataset includes information on station names, their locations, Station IDs, Complex IDs, GTFS Stop IDs, the services that stop there, the type of structure the station is on or in, whether they are in Manhattan’s Central Business District (CBD), and their ADA-accessibility status.

columns.name: Complex ID
columns.description: The Complex ID, or its Complex Master Reference Number.

columns.name: Is Complex
columns.description: TRUE if this is a station complex, and FALSE if not.

columns.name: Number Of Stations In Complex
columns.description: The number of stations within a station complex or 1 if the station is not a station complex.

columns.name: Stop Name
columns.description: The name of the subway station.

columns.name: Display Name
columns.description: The name of the subway station, with the services that serve the station during weekday daytime hours in parenthesis.

columns.name: Constituent Station Names
columns.description: The name of the subway station or of multiple subway stations within one station complex, separated by a semi-colon. For stations that are not in complexes, this is identical to the stop name.

columns.name: Station IDs
columns.description: The ID, or Master Reference Number, for the station. If it is a station complex, multiple IDs are shown, separated by a semi-colon.

columns.name: GTFS Stop IDs
columns.description: The GTFS Stop ID or IDs for the station. If it is a station complex, multiple IDs are shown, separated by a semi-colon.

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: The borough the station is in. Bx for Bronx, B for Brooklyn, M for Manhattan, Q for Queens, SI for Staten Island.

columns.name: CBD
columns.description: This indicates whether or not a station is in Manhattan’s Central Business District (CBD). This value is either TRUE or FALSE.

columns.name: Daytime Routes
columns.description: The subway routes that serve the station during weekdays.

columns.name: Structure Type
columns.description: The type of structure the subway station is located on or in (At Grade, Elevated, Embankment, Open Cut, Subway, Viaduct, etc.). If it is a station complex, and the component stations have different structure types, both are noted, separated by a semi-colon.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: The latitude for the centroid of the station complex.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: The longitude for the centroid of the station complex.

columns.name: ADA
columns.description: 0 if the station is not ADA-accessible, 1 if the station is fully accessible, 2 if the station is partially accessible.

columns.name: ADA Notes
columns.description: Notes on the direction a station is accessible in if it is only accessible in one direction or for a particular platform.
